        "creation_date": 1659380854,
        "body": "<p>You need to aggregate individual articles into single one like:<\/p>\n<pre><code>:toc: macro\n:toclevels: 3\n:toc-title: Contents\n:doctype: book\n:chapter-label:\n\ntoc::[]\n\n:doctype: book\n\ninclude::article1.adoc[]\n\ninclude::article2.adoc[]\n\n...\n\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>and setup maven plugin to compile that single adoc:<\/p>\n<pre class=\"lang-xml prettyprint-override\"><code>&lt;configuration&gt;\n   &lt;sourceDocumentName&gt;single.adoc&lt;/sourceDocumentName&gt;\n&lt;/configuration&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<hr />\n<p>It seems the Q is more about <code>asciidoc<\/code> rather than <code>maven<\/code>...<\/p>\n<p>I believe to support document links we need to create anchors with unique names, something like:<\/p>\n<p>building-tool.adoc:<\/p>\n<pre><code>[#building_tool]\n= Building tool\n\n== Status\nAccepted\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>cloud.adoc:<\/p>\n<pre><code>[#cloud]\n= Cloud\n\n== Status\nAccepted\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>adr-log.adoc:<\/p>\n<pre><code>| 08/07/2022\n| xref:adr/building-tool.adoc#building_tool[Building tool]\n| Accepted\n\n| 08/07/2022\n| xref:adr/cloud.adoc#cloud[Cloud]\n| Accepted\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
        "answer_id": 73198465,
        "question_id": 73198176,
        "last_edit_date": 1659392567
    }],
